CALIFORNIA SHINE THE LIGHT
California law permits customers in California to request certain details about how their personal information is shared with other parties for their own direct marketing purposes. We do not share personal information in this way. Californians may request information about our compliance with this law by contacting us at
privacy@wendys.com
or by sending a letter to:
Wendy’s International, LLC
One Dave Thomas Boulevard, Dublin, OH 43017
Attn: Legal Department – Privacy/Shine the Light
These requests must include your name and “California Shine the Light Privacy Rights Request” and, if sent by mail, must include your street address, city, state, and zip code.
COMPANY APPLICANTS & EMPLOYEES
Within the Wendy’s system, there are restaurants that are Company-owned and operated, as well as restaurants that are owned and operated by independent franchisees. Wendy’s has no control over employment matters at franchisee restaurants.
For more information on our personal information processing in connection with
Wendy's careers see our supplemental privacy policy
here
. These policies are specific to employees working for the Wendy’s company either in Company-owned and operated restaurants or in field/remote positions.
If you are a current or former employee of Wendy's* and a resident of Illinois and want a copy of the Company’s Illinois Biometric Information Privacy Act (BIPA) policy, please contact us at
privacy@wendys.com
.
*Franchisees are solely responsible for employment matters at the restaurants that they own and operate, including hiring, firing, discipline, supervisions, staffing, and scheduling employees.
