Preference Center
When you visit any website, it may store or retrieve information on your browser, in the form of tracking technologies, such as cookies. This information may not directly identify you, but it might be about you, your preferences, or your device. Tracking technologies are generally used to make the site work and provide you with a more personalized, quality web experience.
You can choose to block some types of tracking technologies. To confirm your preferences when visiting Wendy’s website, scroll down to see the different categories of technologies and to change your settings. Be aware, blocking some types of tracking technologies may impact your site experience and the services we are able to offer. To learn more about Wendy’s data processing, your privacy rights, and how to exercise them, review our
Privacy Policy
and
